   <h3> 
     <hr>What does the <span>"Muffin man"</span>, originate from?
</hr>
   </h3>
   <div class="description">
   <section>
<p> "The <span>Muffin Man</span>" is a traditional nursery rhyme, children's song, or children's game of English origin. It has a Roud Folk Song Index number of 7922.<br>

</br>
The rhyme was first recorded in a British manuscript circa 1820, that is preserved in the Bodleian Library with lyrics very similar to those used today: <br>
</section>
</div>

<section class="song">
</br>
"Do you know the  <span>muffin man</span>? <br> </br>
The <span>muffin man</span>, the <span>muffin man</span>.<br> </br>
Do you know the <span>muffin man</span> <br> </br>
Who lives in Drury Lane?"
 <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ec/Happy_smiley_face.png/800px-Happy_smiley_face.png" class="big-smile">
</section>

